commit.message: Couple more quick cleanups.
Another copyright date in need of updating.
Don't need that check anymore; django.setup() always exists.

Fix deprecation warning by using force_str instead of force_text

The two functions are identical in python 3 and force_text will
be removed in Django 4.0

Fix deprecation warning by using gettext_lazy instead of ugettext_lazy

The two functions are identical in python 3 and ugettext_lazy will
be removed in Django 4.0
Bump version numbers.
Clean up some more Python-2-isms.
Cleanup in the FAQ.
Update the upgrade guide.
Cleanup in security documentation.
Cleanup in forms documentation.
Cleanup in the views documentation.
Cleanup in the one-step workflow documentation.
Actually the one-step workflow *doesn't* use that template.
Cleanup in the activation workflow documentation.

Cleanup in the quickstart guide.

This fixes up some of the language to make things clearer, adds
documentation for a template that was previously missing, fixes an old
template-name reference for the one-step workflow, and also lists all
the templates needed for the one-step workflow, instead of just the
form-display template.
Be clear about what to do if you don't want the built-in workflows.
Fix version typo in the install document.
Rework the custom-user documentation.
Ensure pip gets upgraded to latest during test runs.
Couple more explicit paths in tox.ini.
Fix another old-style URL config in the documentation.
Expand and improve test of views breaking on bad custom-user config.
Clean up another stray User reference in tests.base.
And for absolute proof, assert those tests use a custom user model.
Add tests to prove that django-registration works with custom user models.
Let's be incredibly blunt about the custom user stuff.
One more for the spelling list.
Document the HTML5 email validator.
